  "description": [
    "The only properly accredited and publicly announced representative of the railroads who now comes to Tallahassee has openly declared that he de fected the franchise tax in the Legislatures of 1903 and 1905 I refer to Mr Peter Knight who told me this himself in a public place without tying to it the prohibitory string of confidential He made an open fight before the committees of two Legislatures against the imposition of the franchise tax and declares that he is here to do it again He says that the argument used by him which defeated the franchise tax bills in 1903 and 1905 was that the railroads owned onetwentieth of the ds Get Up Steam Aagin property and paid onefifth of the taxes I give Mr Knight credit for sincerity and for honesty in this enuncia tion of his proposition He believes it I am sure of it but itis not true The reports in the Comptrollers office show that the railroads pay taxes in almest exact proportion to the value of their physical property compared with property owned by individuals They show that real and personal property is assessed at about 60 per cent of its valueand that railroads"
